 "cells": [
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Rocket\n",
    "\n",
    "In this example, we will use random convolutions to transform time series."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from sklearn.decomposition import PCA\n",
    "from sklearn.pipeline import make_pipeline\n",
    "\n",
    "from wildboar.datasets import load_dataset\n",
    "from wildboar.transform import RocketTransform\n",
    "\n",
    "random_state = 1234"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "First, we load the dataset."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x, y = load_dataset(\"CBF\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Next, we define the pipeline."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "pca = make_pipeline(\n",
    "    RocketTransform(\n",
    "        n_kernels=1000,\n",
    "        random_state=random_state,\n",
    "    ),\n",
    "    PCA(n_components=3, random_state=random_state),\n",
    ")\n",
    "p = pca.fit_transform(x)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "And, plot the three components with the amount of explained variance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "Text(0.5, 0, 'Component 3 (0.06 variance explained)')"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 576x576 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "var = pca.steps[1][1].explained_variance_ratio_\n",
    "\n",
    "labels, index = np.unique(y, return_inverse=True)\n",
    "colors = plt.cm.rainbow(np.linspace(0, 1, len(labels)))\n",
    "fig = plt.figure(figsize=(8, 8))\n",
    "ax = fig.add_subplot(projection=\"3d\")\n",
    "ax.scatter(p[:, 0], p[:, 1], p[:, 2], color=colors[index, :])\n",
    "ax.set_xlabel(\"Component 1 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[0])\n",
    "ax.set_ylabel(\"Component 2 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[1])\n",
    "ax.set_zlabel(\"Component 3 (%.2f variance explained)\" % var[2])"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": null,

  }
